info.name: Python_APIs
info.description:
# Introduction
What does your API do?

These python APIs are divided into 2. The first is Optical Character Recignition (Aadhar, PAN, and Driving License). This OCR API gives the details of the user such as name, dob, address, pan number, aadhar number, driving license number, and other information. The second API is for Bank Statement Reader (BSR), which gives the data of the transactions made by a user and also classifies it into salary, upi, nach, neft, and imps.

# Overview
Things that the developers should know about


# Authentication
What is the preferred way of using the API?

The preferred way to use the OCR API is that, firstly it takes file input and it must an image or pdf. Extensions allowed are .jpg, .gif, .jpeg, and .png. Further, for BSR API, the input is also a pdf.

# Error Codes
What errors and status codes can a user expect?

Error the users can expect are:
1. File types not allowed.
2. Inavlid images.
3. Input a proper (pan, aadhar, and dl) images
4. PDF not readable.

# Rate limit
Is there a limit to the number of requests a user can send?

No there is no such limit.
